<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,690,1255]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">
Coloration and structure (
<figureCitation box="[445,526,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1657,1679]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,193,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,193,1636]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A – E, dorsal view; F – J, lateral view; K – O, face. A, F, K, Scaphoideus coniceus; B, G, L, Scaphoideus kumamotonis; C, H, M, Scaphoideus maai; D, I, N, Scaphoideus yuani sp. nov; E, J, O, Scaphoideus sagittatus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233532/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">
Figs. 
<number box="[511,526,691,715]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D, I, N, 
<number box="[624,637,691,715]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" value="3.0">3</number>
G) as in 
<taxonomicName box="[740,868,691,714]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coniceus">
<emphasis box="[740,868,691,714]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">S. coniceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but facial markings slightly different, with three anterior marginal lines (
<figureCitation box="[419,486,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1657,1679]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,193,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,193,1636]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A – E, dorsal view; F – J, lateral view; K – O, face. A, F, K, Scaphoideus coniceus; B, G, L, Scaphoideus kumamotonis; C, H, M, Scaphoideus maai; D, I, N, Scaphoideus yuani sp. nov; E, J, O, Scaphoideus sagittatus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233532/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">
Fig. 
<number box="[471,486,727,751]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
N).
</paragraph>
