<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="351" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,690,1255]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis box="[199,375,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view longer than broad, tapering posteriorly, posterior margin conically rounded, with several two tufts of long macrosetae lined subapically and scatter short macrosetae from subapical to middle (
<figureCitation box="[245,326,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[178,1398,345,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[169,1417,329,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Scaphoideus yuani sp. nov. A. Male genital, lateral view; B. Pygofer, ventral view; C. Subgenital plates, styles, connective in dorsal view; D. Style, dorsal view; E. Connective processes, lateral view; F. Aedeagus, lateral view; G. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233542/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">
Fig. 
<number box="[298,326,835,859]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B). Subgenital plate triangular with blunt apex, bearing 
<number box="[994,1031,835,859]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2-3</number>
long macrosetae near base and fine setae along lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[469,555,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[178,1398,345,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[169,1417,329,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Scaphoideus yuani sp. nov. A. Male genital, lateral view; B. Pygofer, ventral view; C. Subgenital plates, styles, connective in dorsal view; D. Style, dorsal view; E. Connective processes, lateral view; F. Aedeagus, lateral view; G. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233542/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">
Fig. 
<number box="[525,555,871,895]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Style with broad anterior part and well developed preapical lobe, apical process slightly curved laterally, tapering to acute apex (
<figureCitation box="[778,859,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[178,1398,345,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[169,1417,329,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Scaphoideus yuani sp. nov. A. Male genital, lateral view; B. Pygofer, ventral view; C. Subgenital plates, styles, connective in dorsal view; D. Style, dorsal view; E. Connective processes, lateral view; F. Aedeagus, lateral view; G. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233542/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">
Fig. 
<number box="[830,859,907,931]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D). Connective with arms divergent, shorter than stem; processes tapered and pointed apically, close together in basal half and then slightly divergent (
<figureCitation box="[1289,1371,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[178,1398,345,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[169,1417,329,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Scaphoideus yuani sp. nov. A. Male genital, lateral view; B. Pygofer, ventral view; C. Subgenital plates, styles, connective in dorsal view; D. Style, dorsal view; E. Connective processes, lateral view; F. Aedeagus, lateral view; G. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233542/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">
Fig. 
<number box="[1342,1371,943,967]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
C, E). Aedeagus with well developed dorsal apodeme, shaft gradually tapered apically and truncated at apex in lateral view, subapical process short, recurved and directed basally in lateral aspect (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1098,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1816,1838]" captionTargetBox="[178,1398,345,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[169,1417,329,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Scaphoideus yuani sp. nov. A. Male genital, lateral view; B. Pygofer, ventral view; C. Subgenital plates, styles, connective in dorsal view; D. Style, dorsal view; E. Connective processes, lateral view; F. Aedeagus, lateral view; G. Aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233542/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">
Fig. 
<number box="[1071,1098,1015,1039]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
F, G).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,690,1255]" box="[199,862,1050,1075]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,1050,1075]" pageId="17" pageNumber="351">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 
<quantity box="[452,531,1051,1075]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[602,660,1051,1075]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="1.0">1mm</quantity>
wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
